CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1955, pg. 8 reads: "Talks About Africa - Mrs. Mabel Little, fifth from left, recently returned missionary, told a capacity audience at Trinity AME Church last Sunday that "Africa, too, has the forward look." Others in picture, left to right, are Mrs. Winifred Burroughs, of the Suehn Mission, Liberia, West Africa; Mrs. A. L. Thomas, Mrs. Clara Harrington, Mrs. B.M. McLinn, Mrs. Little, Mrs. Katie Day, Mrs. Thelma West and Mrs. Ruth West. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Winifred Burroughs, Mrs. A. L. Thomas, Clara Harrington, Mrs. B. M. McLinn, guest speaker Mabel Little, Katie Day, Thelma West, and Ruth West, standing on altar in Trinity AME Church
